The Bauchi State House of Assembly has confirmed Architect Audu Sule Katagum as deputy governor of the state. He was confirmed at a plenary session presided over by the Speaker, Kawuwa Shehu Damina, yesterday. Katagum, the former Chief of Staff, Government House, was nominated by Governor Abubakar in June following the resignation of the former deputy governor, Engineer Nuhu Gidado in May.Â  Governor Abubakar was said to have nominated Katagum after consultations with stakeholders of the All Progressives Congress in the state.